# Adding a new grade (Ч›Ч™ЧЄЧ”)

Use this checklist when introducing another workbook grade (e.g. Ч’Чі) or changing how grades A/B work. Keep changes minimal; extend patterns rather than inventing parallel flows.

## How grades work today (mental model)

- **`GradeId`** lives in `lib/grades.ts`. It drives `parseGradeId` for `/grade/[grade]/*`, Hebrew labels (`gradeLabel`), and any `switch (grade)` branches.
- **Workbook content** is selected in `lib/content/workbook.ts`: grade A в†’ `lib/content/days.ts`; grade B в†’ `lib/content/days-grade-b.ts` (reuses `buildDayFromConcepts` / `DayConcept` from `days.ts`).
- **Plan / ministry UI** uses `getMinistryStrandsForGrade` and `getTotalCurriculumDaysForGrade` in `lib/content/curriculum-plan.ts` (length comes from the workbook for that grade).
- **Progress** is per grade in `lib/progress/storage.ts`: `kids_math.workbook_progress.v2.grade.${grade}`. Grade A has legacy migration from an older unscoped key; grade B had a v1 в†’ v2 pathвЂ”only add migrations if you introduce another predecessor key layout.
- **Final exam**: `FINAL_EXAM_DAY_ID` in `lib/final-exam/config.ts` is `day-29`. `components/screens/DayScreen.tsx` routes that id to `FinalExamScreen`. The exam **bank** and **localStorage** are per grade (`lib/final-exam/picker.ts`, `lib/final-exam/storage.ts`). After submit with pass в‰Ґ `FINAL_EXAM_PASS_PERCENT`, **only grade `"a"`** triggers `POST /api/unlock-grade-b` (see `components/screens/FinalExamScreen.tsx`).
- **Grade B gate**: `middleware.ts` matches `/grade/b/:path*`. Without cookie `kids_math.unlocked_grade_b=1`, requests redirect to `app/grade/b/locked/page.tsx` (API paths under `/grade/b` are excluded so clients can still call unlock).
- **Grade picker**: `app/page.tsx`. **Legacy day URLs**: `app/day/[id]/page.tsx` is hardwired to grade **A** only.

